   Courtesy to the trucks goes both ways. I listen to the truckers on the CB
and haven't heard a bad thing about me. My favorite one is " Did you see
that dang hippy bus blow past me at over 80 mph" or " watch out ahead
there's one of them V-Dub buses going up the hill at 20 mph". When I drive
the highways I always try to work with the truckers. On my last trip to
Cali. I got on the CB and asked a trucker if he would mind if I tailed him
to help block a head wind and he said no problem so I hugged his A#s
(trailer) and let him pull me along for 40 miles or so. Be nice to truckers
and they'll be nice to you.

ronnie   

-----Original Message-----
